## PRACTICAL APPLICATION

```
To hold a ◊:
  1. Receive or create a handle (addressable pointer)
  2. Endorse it ("I mean to return")
  3. Allocate attention slot (can be minimal)
  4. Maintain: refresh before decay, or accept snap

To release a ◊:
  - Complete it (resolution, spring releases energy)
  - Delegate it (split into child ◊ + monitor ◊)
  - Snap it (bankruptcy, spring cut, void signal)
  - Let it decay (entropy, handle → forgotten)

To inherit a ◊:
  - Read the description
  - Compile with intent of continuity
  - Perform re-bind (endorsement act)
  - Now you hold it
```

